987 {
988  /* :nodoc: */
989  rb_cBacktrace = rb_define_class_under(rb_cThread, "Backtrace", rb_cObject);
990  rb_define_alloc_func(rb_cBacktrace, backtrace_alloc);
991  rb_undef_method(CLASS_OF(rb_cBacktrace), "new");
992  rb_marshal_define_compat(rb_cBacktrace, rb_cArray, backtrace_dump_data, backtrace_load_data);
993 
994  /*
995  * An object representation of a stack frame, initialized by
996  * Kernel#caller_locations.
997  *
998  * For example:
999  *
1000  * # caller_locations.rb
1001  * def a(skip)
1002  * caller_locations(skip)
1003  * end
1004  * def b(skip)
1005  * a(skip)
1006  * end
1007  * def c(skip)
1008  * b(skip)
1009  * end
1010  *
1011  * c(0..2).map do |call|
1012  * puts call.to_s
1013  * end
1014  *
1015  * Running <code>ruby caller_locations.rb</code> will produce:
1016  *
1017  * caller_locations.rb:2:in `a'
1018  * caller_locations.rb:5:in `b'
1019  * caller_locations.rb:8:in `c'
1020  *
1021  * Here's another example with a slightly different result:
1022  *
1023  * # foo.rb
1024  * class Foo
1025  * attr_accessor :locations
1026  * def initialize(skip)
1027  * @locations = caller_locations(skip)
1028  * end
1029  * end
1030  *
1031  * Foo.new(0..2).locations.map do |call|
1032  * puts call.to_s
1033  * end
1034  *
1035  * Now run <code>ruby foo.rb</code> and you should see:
1036  *
1037  * init.rb:4:in `initialize'
1038  * init.rb:8:in `new'
1039  * init.rb:8:in `<main>'
1040  */
1041  rb_cBacktraceLocation = rb_define_class_under(rb_cBacktrace, "Location", rb_cObject);
1042  rb_undef_alloc_func(rb_cBacktraceLocation);
1043  rb_undef_method(CLASS_OF(rb_cBacktraceLocation), "new");
1044  rb_define_method(rb_cBacktraceLocation, "lineno", location_lineno_m, 0);
1045  rb_define_method(rb_cBacktraceLocation, "label", location_label_m, 0);
1046  rb_define_method(rb_cBacktraceLocation, "base_label", location_base_label_m, 0);
1047  rb_define_method(rb_cBacktraceLocation, "path", location_path_m, 0);
1048  rb_define_method(rb_cBacktraceLocation, "absolute_path", location_absolute_path_m, 0);
1049  rb_define_method(rb_cBacktraceLocation, "to_s", location_to_str_m, 0);
1050  rb_define_method(rb_cBacktraceLocation, "inspect", location_inspect_m, 0);
1051 
1052  rb_define_global_function("caller", rb_f_caller, -1);
1053  rb_define_global_function("caller_locations", rb_f_caller_locations, -1);
1054 }

3270 {
3271  const char *s, *b, *fend;
3272  char *buf, *p, *pend, *root;
3273  size_t buflen, bdiff;
3274  int tainted;
3275  rb_encoding *enc, *fsenc = rb_filesystem_encoding();
3276 
3277  s = StringValuePtr(fname);
3278  fend = s + RSTRING_LEN(fname);
3279  enc = rb_enc_get(fname);
3280  BUFINIT();
3281  tainted = OBJ_TAINTED(fname);
3282 
3283  if (s[0] == '~' && abs_mode == 0) { /* execute only if NOT absolute_path() */
3284  long userlen = 0;
3285  tainted = 1;
3286  if (isdirsep(s[1]) || s[1] == '\0') {
3287  buf = 0;
3288  b = 0;
3289  rb_str_set_len(result, 0);
3290  if (*++s) ++s;
3291  rb_default_home_dir(result);
3292  }
3293  else {
3294  s = nextdirsep(b = s, fend, enc);
3295  b++; /* b[0] is '~' */
3296  userlen = s - b;
3297  BUFCHECK(bdiff + userlen >= buflen);
3298  memcpy(p, b, userlen);
3299  ENC_CODERANGE_CLEAR(result);
3300  rb_str_set_len(result, userlen);
3301  rb_enc_associate(result, enc);
3302  rb_home_dir_of(result, result);
3303  buf = p + 1;
3304  p += userlen;
3305  }
3306  if (!rb_is_absolute_path(RSTRING_PTR(result))) {
3307  if (userlen) {
3308  rb_enc_raise(enc, rb_eArgError, "non-absolute home of %.*s%.0"PRIsVALUE,
3309  (int)userlen, b, fname);
3310  }
3311  else {
3312  rb_raise(rb_eArgError, "non-absolute home");
3313  }
3314  }
3315  BUFINIT();
3316  p = pend;
3317  }
3318 #ifdef DOSISH_DRIVE_LETTER
3319  /* skip drive letter */
3320  else if (has_drive_letter(s)) {
3321  if (isdirsep(s[2])) {
3322  /* specified drive letter, and full path */
3323  /* skip drive letter */
3324  BUFCHECK(bdiff + 2 >= buflen);
3325  memcpy(p, s, 2);
3326  p += 2;
3327  s += 2;
3328  rb_enc_copy(result, fname);
3329  }
3330  else {
3331  /* specified drive, but not full path */
3332  int same = 0;
3333  if (!NIL_P(dname) && !not_same_drive(dname, s[0])) {
3334  rb_file_expand_path_internal(dname, Qnil, abs_mode, long_name, result);
3335  BUFINIT();
3336  if (has_drive_letter(p) && TOLOWER(p[0]) == TOLOWER(s[0])) {
3337  /* ok, same drive */
3338  same = 1;
3339  }
3340  }
3341  if (!same) {
3342  char *e = append_fspath(result, fname, getcwdofdrv(*s), &enc, fsenc);
3343  tainted = 1;
3344  BUFINIT();
3345  p = e;
3346  }
3347  else {
3348  rb_enc_associate(result, enc = rb_enc_check(result, fname));
3349  p = pend;
3350  }
3351  p = chompdirsep(skiproot(buf, p, enc), p, enc);
3352  s += 2;
3353  }
3354  }
3355 #endif
3356  else if (!rb_is_absolute_path(s)) {
3357  if (!NIL_P(dname)) {
3358  rb_file_expand_path_internal(dname, Qnil, abs_mode, long_name, result);
3359  rb_enc_associate(result, rb_enc_check(result, fname));
3360  BUFINIT();
3361  p = pend;
3362  }
3363  else {
3364  char *e = append_fspath(result, fname, my_getcwd(), &enc, fsenc);
3365  tainted = 1;
3366  BUFINIT();
3367  p = e;
3368  }
3369 #if defined DOSISH || defined __CYGWIN__
3370  if (isdirsep(*s)) {
3371  /* specified full path, but not drive letter nor UNC */
3372  /* we need to get the drive letter or UNC share name */
3373  p = skipprefix(buf, p, enc);
3374  }
3375  else
3376 #endif
3377  p = chompdirsep(skiproot(buf, p, enc), p, enc);
3378  }
3379  else {
3380  size_t len;
3381  b = s;
3382  do s++; while (isdirsep(*s));
3383  len = s - b;
3384  p = buf + len;
3385  BUFCHECK(bdiff >= buflen);
3386  memset(buf, '/', len);
3387  rb_str_set_len(result, len);
3388  rb_enc_associate(result, rb_enc_check(result, fname));
3389  }
3390  if (p > buf && p[-1] == '/')
3391  --p;
3392  else {
3393  rb_str_set_len(result, p-buf);
3394  BUFCHECK(bdiff + 1 >= buflen);
3395  *p = '/';
3396  }
3397 
3398  rb_str_set_len(result, p-buf+1);
3399  BUFCHECK(bdiff + 1 >= buflen);
3400  p[1] = 0;
3401  root = skipprefix(buf, p+1, enc);
3402 
3403  b = s;
3404  while (*s) {
3405  switch (*s) {
3406  case '.':
3407  if (b == s++) { /* beginning of path element */
3408  switch (*s) {
3409  case '\0':
3410  b = s;
3411  break;
3412  case '.':
3413  if (*(s+1) == '\0' || isdirsep(*(s+1))) {
3414  /* We must go back to the parent */
3415  char *n;
3416  *p = '\0';
3417  if (!(n = strrdirsep(root, p, enc))) {
3418  *p = '/';
3419  }
3420  else {
3421  p = n;
3422  }
3423  b = ++s;
3424  }
3425 #if USE_NTFS
3426  else {
3427  do ++s; while (istrailinggarbage(*s));
3428  }
3429 #endif
3430  break;
3431  case '/':
3432 #if defined DOSISH || defined __CYGWIN__
3433  case '\\':
3434 #endif
3435  b = ++s;
3436  break;
3437  default:
3438  /* ordinary path element, beginning don't move */
3439  break;
3440  }
3441  }
3442 #if USE_NTFS
3443  else {
3444  --s;
3445  case ' ': {
3446  const char *e = s;
3447  while (s < fend && istrailinggarbage(*s)) s++;
3448  if (!*s) {
3449  s = e;
3450  goto endpath;
3451  }
3452  }
3453  }
3454 #endif
3455  break;
3456  case '/':
3457 #if defined DOSISH || defined __CYGWIN__
3458  case '\\':
3459 #endif
3460  if (s > b) {
3461  WITH_ROOTDIFF(BUFCOPY(b, s-b));
3462  *p = '/';
3463  }
3464  b = ++s;
3465  break;
3466  default:
3467 #ifdef __APPLE__
3468  {
3469  int n = ignored_char_p(s, fend, enc);
3470  if (n) {
3471  if (s > b) {
3472  WITH_ROOTDIFF(BUFCOPY(b, s-b));
3473  *p = '\0';
3474  }
3475  b = s += n;
3476  break;
3477  }
3478  }
3479 #endif
3480  Inc(s, fend, enc);
3481  break;
3482  }
3483  }
3484 
3485  if (s > b) {
3486 #if USE_NTFS
3487  static const char prime[] = ":$DATA";
3488  enum {prime_len = sizeof(prime) -1};
3489  endpath:
3490  if (s > b + prime_len && strncasecmp(s - prime_len, prime, prime_len) == 0) {
3491  /* alias of stream */
3492  /* get rid of a bug of x64 VC++ */
3493  if (*(s - (prime_len+1)) == ':') {
3494  s -= prime_len + 1; /* prime */
3495  }
3496  else if (memchr(b, ':', s - prime_len - b)) {
3497  s -= prime_len; /* alternative */
3498  }
3499  }
3500 #endif
3501  BUFCOPY(b, s-b);
3502  rb_str_set_len(result, p-buf);
3503  }
3504  if (p == skiproot(buf, p + !!*p, enc) - 1) p++;
3505 
3506 #if USE_NTFS
3507  *p = '\0';
3508  if ((s = strrdirsep(b = buf, p, enc)) != 0 && !strpbrk(s, "*?")) {
3509  VALUE tmp, v;

3511  rb_encoding *enc;

3535 #ifdef HAVE_CYGWIN_CONV_PATH

222  flags = fcntl(fd, F_GETFD); /* should not fail except EBADF. */
223  if (flags == -1) {
224  rb_bug("rb_maygvl_fd_fix_cloexec: fcntl(%d, F_GETFD) failed: %s", fd, strerror(errno));
225  }
226  if (fd <= 2)
227  flags2 = flags & ~FD_CLOEXEC; /* Clear CLOEXEC for standard file descriptors: 0, 1, 2. */
228  else
229  flags2 = flags | FD_CLOEXEC; /* Set CLOEXEC for non-standard file descriptors: 3, 4, 5, ... */
230  if (flags != flags2) {
231  ret = fcntl(fd, F_SETFD, flags2);
232  if (ret == -1) {
233  rb_bug("rb_maygvl_fd_fix_cloexec: fcntl(%d, F_SETFD, %d) failed: %s", fd, flags2, strerror(errno));
234  }
235  }
236 #endif
237 }

3101 {
3102  /* Arguments ndigits, decpt, sign are similar to those
3103  of ecvt and fcvt; trailing zeros are suppressed from
3104  the returned string. If not null, *rve is set to point
3105  to the end of the return value. If d is +-Infinity or NaN,
3106  then *decpt is set to 9999.
3107 
3108  mode:
3109  0 ==> shortest string that yields d when read in
3110  and rounded to nearest.
3111  1 ==> like 0, but with Steele & White stopping rule;
3112  e.g. with IEEE P754 arithmetic , mode 0 gives
3113  1e23 whereas mode 1 gives 9.999999999999999e22.
3114  2 ==> max(1,ndigits) significant digits. This gives a
3115  return value similar to that of ecvt, except
3116  that trailing zeros are suppressed.
3117  3 ==> through ndigits past the decimal point. This
3118  gives a return value similar to that from fcvt,
3119  except that trailing zeros are suppressed, and
3120  ndigits can be negative.
3121  4,5 ==> similar to 2 and 3, respectively, but (in
3122  round-nearest mode) with the tests of mode 0 to
3123  possibly return a shorter string that rounds to d.
3124  With IEEE arithmetic and compilation with
3125  -DHonor_FLT_ROUNDS, modes 4 and 5 behave the same
3126  as modes 2 and 3 when FLT_ROUNDS != 1.
3127  6-9 ==> Debugging modes similar to mode - 4: don't try
3128  fast floating-point estimate (if applicable).
3129 
3130  Values of mode other than 0-9 are treated as mode 0.
3131 
3132  Sufficient space is allocated to the return value
3133  to hold the suppressed trailing zeros.
3134  */
3135 
3136  int bbits, b2, b5, be, dig, i, ieps, ilim, ilim0, ilim1,
3137  j, j1, k, k0, k_check, leftright, m2, m5, s2, s5,

3153 #endif

3156

3158  if (dtoa_result) {
3159  freedtoa(dtoa_result);
3160  dtoa_result = 0;
3161  }
3162 #endif
3163 
3164  if (word0(d) & Sign_bit) {
3165  /* set sign for everything, including 0's and NaNs */
3166  *sign = 1;
3167  word0(d) &= ~Sign_bit; /* clear sign bit */
3168  }
3169  else
3170  *sign = 0;
3171 
3172 #if defined(IEEE_Arith) + defined(VAX)
3173 #ifdef IEEE_Arith

3175 #else

3177 #endif

3181 #ifdef IEEE_Arith

3187 #endif

3199 #endif

3201  if ((rounding = Flt_Rounds) >= 2) {
3202  if (*sign)
3203  rounding = rounding == 2 ? 0 : 2;
3204  else
3205  if (rounding != 2)
3206  rounding = 0;
3207  }
3208 #endif
3209 
3210  b = d2b(dval(d), &be, &bbits);
3211 #ifdef Sudden_Underflow
3212  i = (int)(word0(d) >> Exp_shift1 & (Exp_mask>>Exp_shift1));
3213 #else
3214  if ((i = (int)(word0(d) >> Exp_shift1 & (Exp_mask>>Exp_shift1))) != 0) {
3215 #endif

3217  word0(d2) &= Frac_mask1;

3223 
3224  /* log(x) ~=~ log(1.5) + (x-1.5)/1.5
3225  * log10(x) = log(x) / log(10)
3226  * ~=~ log(1.5)/log(10) + (x-1.5)/(1.5*log(10))
3227  * log10(d) = (i-Bias)*log(2)/log(10) + log10(d2)
3228  *
3229  * This suggests computing an approximation k to log10(d) by
3230  *
3231  * k = (i - Bias)*0.301029995663981
3232  * + ( (d2-1.5)*0.289529654602168 + 0.176091259055681 );
3233  *
3234  * We want k to be too large rather than too small.
3235  * The error in the first-order Taylor series approximation
3236  * is in our favor, so we just round up the constant enough
3237  * to compensate for any error in the multiplication of
3238  * (i - Bias) by 0.301029995663981; since |i - Bias| <= 1077,
3239  * and 1077 * 0.30103 * 2^-52 ~=~ 7.2e-14,
3240  * adding 1e-13 to the constant term more than suffices.
3241  * Hence we adjust the constant term to 0.1760912590558.
3242  * (We could get a more accurate k by invoking log10,
3243  * but this is probably not worthwhile.)
3244  */

3249  i += j;

3257  i = bbits + be + (Bias + (P-1) - 1);

3259  : word1(d) << (32 - i);
3260  dval(d2) = x;
3261  word0(d2) -= 31*Exp_msk1; /* adjust exponent */
3262  i -= (Bias + (P-1) - 1) + 1;
3263  denorm = 1;
3264  }
3265 #endif
3266  ds = (dval(d2)-1.5)*0.289529654602168 + 0.1760912590558 + i*0.301029995663981;
3267  k = (int)ds;
3268  if (ds < 0. && ds != k)
3269  k--; /* want k = floor(ds) */
3270  k_check = 1;
3271  if (k >= 0 && k <= Ten_pmax) {
3272  if (dval(d) < tens[k])
3273  k--;
3274  k_check = 0;
3275  }
3276  j = bbits - i - 1;
3277  if (j >= 0) {
3278  b2 = 0;
3279  s2 = j;
3280  }
3281  else {
3282  b2 = -j;
3283  s2 = 0;
3284  }

3289  }

3293  s5 = 0;

3295  if (mode < 0 || mode > 9)

3297 
3298 #ifndef SET_INEXACT
3299 #ifdef Check_FLT_ROUNDS
3300  try_quick = Rounding == 1;
3301 #else
3302  try_quick = 1;
3303 #endif
3304 #endif /*SET_INEXACT*/
3305 
3306  if (mode > 5) {
3307  mode -= 4;
3308  try_quick = 0;
3309  }
3310  leftright = 1;
3311  ilim = ilim1 = -1;
3312  switch (mode) {
3313  case 0:
3314  case 1:
3315  i = 18;
3316  ndigits = 0;
3317  break;
3318  case 2:
3319  leftright = 0;
3320  /* no break */
3321  case 4:
3322  if (ndigits <= 0)
3323  ndigits = 1;

3325  break;
3326  case 3:
3327  leftright = 0;
3328  /* no break */
3329  case 5:

3331  ilim = i;
3332  ilim1 = i - 1;
3333  if (i <= 0)

3344

3346 
3347  i = 0;
3348  dval(d2) = dval(d);

3351  ieps = 2; /* conservative */

3355  if (j & Bletch) {

3357  j &= Bletch - 1;
3358  dval(d) /= bigtens[n_bigtens-1];
3359  ieps++;
3360  }
3361  for (; j; j >>= 1, i++)
3362  if (j & 1) {
3363  ieps++;
3364  ds *= bigtens[i];
3365  }
3366  dval(d) /= ds;
3367  }
3368  else if ((j1 = -k) != 0) {
3369  dval(d) *= tens[j1 & 0xf];
3370  for (j = j1 >> 4; j; j >>= 1, i++)
3371  if (j & 1) {
3372  ieps++;
3373  dval(d) *= bigtens[i];
3374  }
3375  }
3376  if (k_check && dval(d) < 1. && ilim > 0) {
3377  if (ilim1 <= 0)
3378  goto fast_failed;
3379  ilim = ilim1;
3380  k--;
3381  dval(d) *= 10.;
3382  ieps++;
3383  }
3384  dval(eps) = ieps*dval(d) + 7.;
3385  word0(eps) -= (P-1)*Exp_msk1;

3390  goto one_digit;
3391  if (dval(d) < -dval(eps))
3392  goto no_digits;

3394  }

3398  * generating digits needed.
3399  */
3400  dval(eps) = 0.5/tens[ilim-1] - dval(eps);
3401  for (i = 0;;) {

3404  *s++ = '0' + (int)L;

3409  if (++i >= ilim)

3413  }
3414  }
3415  else {
3416 #endif
3417  /* Generate ilim digits, then fix them up. */
3418  dval(eps) *= tens[ilim-1];
3419  for (i = 1;; i++, dval(d) *= 10.) {
3420  L = (Long)(dval(d));
3421  if (!(dval(d) -= L))
3422  ilim = i;
3423  *s++ = '0' + (int)L;
3424  if (i == ilim) {
3425  if (dval(d) > 0.5 + dval(eps))
3426  goto bump_up;
3427  else if (dval(d) < 0.5 - dval(eps)) {
3428  while (*--s == '0') ;
3429  s++;
3430  goto ret1;
3431  }
3432  break;
3433  }
3434  }
3435 #ifndef No_leftright
3436  }
3437 #endif
3438 fast_failed:
3439  s = s0;
3440  dval(d) = dval(d2);
3441  k = k0;
3442  ilim = ilim0;
3443  }
3444 
3445  /* Do we have a "small" integer? */
3446 
3447  if (be >= 0 && k <= Int_max) {
3448  /* Yes. */
3449  ds = tens[k];
3450  if (ndigits < 0 && ilim <= 0) {
3451  S = mhi = 0;
3452  if (ilim < 0 || dval(d) <= 5*ds)
3453  goto no_digits;
3454  goto one_digit;
3455  }
3456  for (i = 1;; i++, dval(d) *= 10.) {
3457  L = (Long)(dval(d) / ds);
3458  dval(d) -= L*ds;
3459 #ifdef Check_FLT_ROUNDS
3460  /* If FLT_ROUNDS == 2, L will usually be high by 1 */
3461  if (dval(d) < 0) {
3462  L--;
3463  dval(d) += ds;
3464  }
3465 #endif
3466  *s++ = '0' + (int)L;
3467  if (!dval(d)) {
3468 #ifdef SET_INEXACT
3469  inexact = 0;
3470 #endif
3471  break;
3472  }
3473  if (i == ilim) {
3474 #ifdef Honor_FLT_ROUNDS
3475  if (mode > 1)
3476  switch (rounding) {
3477  case 0: goto ret1;
3478  case 2: goto bump_up;
3479  }
3480 #endif
3481  dval(d) += dval(d);
3482  if (dval(d) > ds || (dval(d) == ds && (L & 1))) {
3483 bump_up:
3484  while (*--s == '9')
3485  if (s == s0) {
3486  k++;
3487  *s = '0';
3488  break;
3489  }
3490  ++*s++;
3491  }
3492  break;
3493  }
3494  }
3495  goto ret1;
3496  }
3497 
3498  m2 = b2;
3499  m5 = b5;
3500  if (leftright) {
3501  i =
3502 #ifndef Sudden_Underflow
3503  denorm ? be + (Bias + (P-1) - 1 + 1) :
3504 #endif
3505 #ifdef IBM
3506  1 + 4*P - 3 - bbits + ((bbits + be - 1) & 3);
3507 #else
3508  1 + P - bbits;
3509 #endif
3510  b2 += i;
3511  s2 += i;
3512  mhi = i2b(1);
3513  }
3514  if (m2 > 0 && s2 > 0) {
3515  i = m2 < s2 ? m2 : s2;
3516  b2 -= i;
3517  m2 -= i;
3518  s2 -= i;
3519  }
3520  if (b5 > 0) {
3521  if (leftright) {
3522  if (m5 > 0) {
3523  mhi = pow5mult(mhi, m5);
3524  b1 = mult(mhi, b);
3525  Bfree(b);
3526  b = b1;
3527  }
3528  if ((j = b5 - m5) != 0)
3529  b = pow5mult(b, j);
3530  }
3531  else
3532  b = pow5mult(b, b5);
3533  }
3534  S = i2b(1);
3535  if (s5 > 0)
3536  S = pow5mult(S, s5);
3537 
3538  /* Check for special case that d is a normalized power of 2. */
3539 
3540  spec_case = 0;
3541  if ((mode < 2 || leftright)
3542 #ifdef Honor_FLT_ROUNDS
3543  && rounding == 1
3544 #endif
3545  ) {
3546  if (!word1(d) && !(word0(d) & Bndry_mask)
3547 #ifndef Sudden_Underflow
3548  && word0(d) & (Exp_mask & ~Exp_msk1)
3549 #endif
3550  ) {
3551  /* The special case */
3552  b2 += Log2P;
3553  s2 += Log2P;
3554  spec_case = 1;
3555  }
3556  }
3557 
3558  /* Arrange for convenient computation of quotients:
3559  * shift left if necessary so divisor has 4 leading 0 bits.
3560  *
3561  * Perhaps we should just compute leading 28 bits of S once
3562  * and for all and pass them and a shift to quorem, so it
3563  * can do shifts and ors to compute the numerator for q.
3564  */
3565 #ifdef Pack_32
3566  if ((i = ((s5 ? 32 - hi0bits(S->x[S->wds-1]) : 1) + s2) & 0x1f) != 0)
3567  i = 32 - i;
3568 #else
3569  if ((i = ((s5 ? 32 - hi0bits(S->x[S->wds-1]) : 1) + s2) & 0xf) != 0)
3570  i = 16 - i;
3571 #endif
3572  if (i > 4) {
3573  i -= 4;
3574  b2 += i;
3575  m2 += i;
3576  s2 += i;
3577  }
3578  else if (i < 4) {
3579  i += 28;
3580  b2 += i;
3581  m2 += i;
3582  s2 += i;
3583  }
3584  if (b2 > 0)
3585  b = lshift(b, b2);
3586  if (s2 > 0)
3587  S = lshift(S, s2);
3588  if (k_check) {
3589  if (cmp(b,S) < 0) {
3590  k--;
3591  b = multadd(b, 10, 0); /* we botched the k estimate */
3592  if (leftright)
3593  mhi = multadd(mhi, 10, 0);
3594  ilim = ilim1;
3595  }
3596  }
3597  if (ilim <= 0 && (mode == 3 || mode == 5)) {
3598  if (ilim < 0 || cmp(b,S = multadd(S,5,0)) <= 0) {
3599  /* no digits, fcvt style */
3600 no_digits:
3601  k = -1 - ndigits;
3602  goto ret;
3603  }
3604 one_digit:
3605  *s++ = '1';
3606  k++;
3607  goto ret;
3608  }
3609  if (leftright) {
3610  if (m2 > 0)
3611  mhi = lshift(mhi, m2);
3612 
3613  /* Compute mlo -- check for special case
3614  * that d is a normalized power of 2.
3615  */
3616 
3617  mlo = mhi;
3618  if (spec_case) {
3619  mhi = Balloc(mhi->k);
3620  Bcopy(mhi, mlo);
3621  mhi = lshift(mhi, Log2P);
3622  }
3623 
3624  for (i = 1;;i++) {
3625  dig = quorem(b,S) + '0';
3626  /* Do we yet have the shortest decimal string
3627  * that will round to d?
3628  */

3630  delta = diff(S, mhi);
3631  j1 = delta->sign ? 1 : cmp(b, delta);

3643 #ifdef SET_INEXACT

3646 #endif

3648  goto ret;
3649  }
3650 #endif
3651  if (j < 0 || (j == 0 && mode != 1
3652 #ifndef ROUND_BIASED
3653  && !(word1(d) & 1)
3654 #endif
3655  )) {
3656  if (!b->x[0] && b->wds <= 1) {
3657 #ifdef SET_INEXACT
3658  inexact = 0;
3659 #endif
3660  goto accept_dig;
3661  }
3662 #ifdef Honor_FLT_ROUNDS
3663  if (mode > 1)
3664  switch (rounding) {
3665  case 0: goto accept_dig;
3666  case 2: goto keep_dig;
3667  }
3668 #endif /*Honor_FLT_ROUNDS*/
3669  if (j1 > 0) {
3670  b = lshift(b, 1);
3671  j1 = cmp(b, S);
3672  if ((j1 > 0 || (j1 == 0 && (dig & 1))) && dig++ == '9')
3673  goto round_9_up;
3674  }

3678  }

3887  if (ndigits == 0) /* dtoa() compatibility */
3888  ndigits = 1;
3889 
3890  /*
3891  * If ndigits < 0, we are expected to auto-size, so we allocate
3892  * enough space for all the digits.
3893  */
3894  bufsize = (ndigits > 0) ? ndigits : SIGFIGS;
3895  s0 = rv_alloc(bufsize+1);
3896 
3897  /* Round to the desired number of digits. */
3898  if (SIGFIGS > ndigits && ndigits > 0) {
3899  float redux = 1.0f;
3900  int offset = 4 * ndigits + DBL_MAX_EXP - 4 - DBL_MANT_DIG;
3901  dexp_set(u, offset);
3902  u.d += redux;
3903  u.d -= redux;
3904  *decpt += dexp_get(u) - offset;
3905  }
3906 
3907  manh = dmanh_get(u);
3908  manl = dmanl_get(u);
3909  *s0 = '1';
3910  for (s = s0 + 1; s < s0 + bufsize; s++) {
3911  *s = xdigs[(manh >> (DBL_MANH_SIZE - 4)) & 0xf];
3912  manh = (manh << 4) | (manl >> (DBL_MANL_SIZE - 4));
3913  manl <<= 4;
3914  }
3915 
3916  /* If ndigits < 0, we are expected to auto-size the precision. */
3917  if (ndigits < 0) {
3918  for (ndigits = SIGFIGS; s0[ndigits - 1] == '0'; ndigits--)
3919  ;
3920  }
3921 
3922  s = s0 + ndigits;
3923  *s = '\0';
3924  if (rve != NULL)
3925  *rve = s;
3926  return (s0);
3927 }
